DOS-PORT (patch 0089, Phase 9 wave 20 iter W20A2). Adds
SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_OFF=1 (strict-1 match per CLAUDE.md
convention; default OFF) — when set, the engine init path:

  1. Omits SDL_INIT_AUDIO from the SDL_Init flags (so the SDL3-DOS
     audio backend never runs SB16 DSP probe → never hooks the IRQ-5
     handler → never starts the audio mixer thread).
  2. Skips SoundManager::init() (skips MIX_CreateMixerDevice +
     Organya / Pixtone init).

This is DEEPER than the pre-existing DOSKUTSU_NO_AUDIO=1 diagnostic
(which only skipped SoundManager::init() but still inited the SDL
audio subsystem and hooked the SB16 IRQ). For the W20A2 ablation
hypothesis test, the deeper skip is required: we need the audio IRQ
removed entirely from the timing equation.

Hypothesis test (per docs/PHASE9-WAVE-20-COLD-PICKUP.md plan +
memory/wave_20_misc_slice_in_flip_body.md): does flip_inner late-block
growth correlate with audio IRQ wall-clock cost?

Possible outcomes:
  flip_inner stays ~18 ms early AND ~18 ms late (no growth)
    → audio-IRQ wall-clock hypothesis CONFIRMED for late-block
      degradation. The audio-off CEILING at 25.6 fps in early blocks
      is a separate question (W20B answers that).
  flip_inner stays ~18 ms early but climbs in late blocks
    → audio is NOT the wall-clock culprit; something else correlates
      with late-game state. Pivot to W20B without committing the
      audio-IRQ rewrite.

Either way, the early-block CEILING at 25.6 fps with audio_mix=0 is
already a fixed observable from W20A — W20A2 only addresses the
late-block GROWTH question.

Implementation:
  src/main.cpp ~line 500: read AUDIO_OFF env var into _audio_off bool;
    when set, mask out SDL_INIT_AUDIO from _sdl_init_flags and emit a
    LOG_INFO line so DEBUG.LOG self-describes the iter config.
  src/main.cpp ~line 542: when _audio_off, skip SoundManager::init()
    via a new branch that takes precedence over the existing
    DOSKUTSU_NO_AUDIO branch (different scope; the two should not
    stack but if both are set AUDIO_OFF wins).

Shutdown safety: SoundManager::shutdown() (called unconditionally
near program exit) is gated on `if (_mixer)` so calling it on an
uninit'd SoundManager is a safe no-op. Organya / Pixtone shutdowns
are similarly defensive. Verified by reading
vendor/nxengine-evo/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp:190.

W20A2 iter env stack (single PLAY, ~5 min wall time):
  SET DOSKUTSU_LOG_TAG=W20A2
  SET SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FLIP_INSTR=1
  SET SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_LFB=1
  SET SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRECT_VESA=1
  SET SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_OFF=1
  DOSKUTSU.EXE

LOG_TAG=W20A2 is 5 chars (within the 8.3 cap per
memory/log_tag_8_3_limit.md).

Documentation: docs/BOOT.md gains an SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_OFF=1
entry under the Diagnostic / development section per
memory/env_vars_document_in_user_docs.md.

Test plan (subsequent task):
  - DOSBox-X smoke (build-qa): with the env set, DEBUG.LOG should
    show "SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_OFF=1 — skipping SDL_INIT_AUDIO ..."
    and NO Mix_OpenAudio / SoundManager::init success log lines. With
    env unset, behavior identical to wave-20 baseline.
  - Real-HW iter W20A2 (realhw): bundle the new binary with
    CWSDPMI.EXE + a PLAY1.BAT-W20A2 setting the full env stack above.

